<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casio_fx-7000G" title=3D"Casio fx-=
7000G">Casio fx-7000G</a>; the world's first graphing calculator</figcaptio=
n></figure>
<p>An early graphing calculator was designed in 1921 by electrical engineer=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edith_Clarke" title=3D"Edith Clar=
ke">Edith Clarke</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-1"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-:10_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-:10-2"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph=
ing_calculator#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The calculator was used to solve pro=
blems with electrical power line transmission.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:72_4-0" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calcu=
lator#cite_note-:72-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casio" title=3D"Casio">Casi=
o</a> produced the first commercially available graphing calculator in 1985=
. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sharp_Corporation" title=3D"Shar=
p Corporation">Sharp</a> produced its first graphing calculator in 1986, wi=
th <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hewlett-Packard" title=3D"Hewle=
tt-Packard">Hewlett Packard</a> following in 1988, and <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas_Instruments" title=3D"Texas Instruments">Texas I=
nstruments</a> in 1990.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-5"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Features">Features</h2><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGraphing_calculator&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Features"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Computer_algebra_systems">C=
omputer algebra systems</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DGraphing_calculator&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D=
"Edit section: Computer algebra systems"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:A_graph_GIF_being_captured_from_a_TI-89_Titan=
ium.gif" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia=
.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cf/A_graph_GIF_being_captured_from_a_TI-89_Titaniu=
m.gif" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"240" height=3D"150" class=3D"mw-file-ele=
ment" data-file-width=3D"240" data-file-height=3D"150"></a><figcaption>The =
Texas Instruments TI-89 Titanium graphing a sine type graph. (Generated fro=
m TI ScreenCapture software on TI Connect CE.)</figcaption></figure>
<p>Some graphing calculators have a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Computer_algebra_system" title=3D"Computer algebra system">computer algeb=
ra system</a> (CAS), which means that they are capable of producing symboli=
c results. These calculators can manipulate algebraic expressions, performi=
ng operations such as factor, expand, and simplify. In addition, they can g=
ive answers in exact form without numerical approximations.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphin=
g_calculator#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Calculators that have a computer algeb=
ra system are called symbolic or CAS calculators.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Laboratory_usage">Laborator=
y usage</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGrap=
hing_calculator&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: L=
aboratory usage"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket=
">]</span></span></div>
<p>Many graphing calculators can be attached to devices like electronic <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermometer" title=3D"Thermometer">th=
ermometers</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PH" title=3D"PH">p=
H</a> gauges, weather instruments, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Decibel" title=3D"Decibel">decibel</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Light_meter" title=3D"Light meter">light meters</a>, <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accelerometer" title=3D"Accelerometer">acceler=
ometers</a>, and other sensors and therefore function as <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_logger" title=3D"Data logger">data loggers</a>,=
 as well as WiFi or other communication modules for monitoring, polling and=
 interaction with the teacher. Student laboratory exercises with data from =
such devices enhances learning of math, especially statistics and mechanics=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
