file-element" data-file-width=3D"754" data-file-height=3D"560"></a><figcapt=
ion>Graphing calculators are sometimes used for <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Mobile_game#Calculator_games" title=3D"Mobile game">gaming</a=
>.</figcaption></figure>
<p>Since graphing calculators are typically user-programmable, they are als=
o widely used for utilities and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ca=
lculator_gaming" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Calculator gaming">calculat=
or gaming</a>, with a sizable body of user-created game software on most po=
pular platforms.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_8-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-:0-8"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> The ability to create games and utilities has spurred the creation of cal=
culator application sites (e.g., <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
emetech" title=3D"Cemetech">Cemetech</a>) which, in some cases, may offer p=
rograms created using calculators' <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Assembly_language" title=3D"Assembly language">assembly language</a>. Even=
 though handheld gaming devices fall in a similar price range, graphing cal=
culators offer superior math programming capability for math based games. H=
owever, due to poor display resolution, slow processor speed and lack of a =
dedicated keyboard, they are mostly preferred only by high school students.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_8-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-:0-8"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>For developers and advanced users, including researchers, analysts, =
and gamers, third-party software development involving firmware modificatio=
ns=E2=80=94whether to enhance gaming performance or to exploit capabilities=
 beyond those documented in official data sheets and programming languages=
=E2=80=94remains a contentious issue. Manufacturers and educational authori=
ties express concern that such modifications may facilitate unfair calculat=
or use during standardized high school and college examinations, where thes=
e devices are subject to strict regulations.
</p>
