<p>Attitudes towards graphing and other calculators in education have evolv=
ed over the years, and while some jurisdictions prohibit their use for clas=
swork or exams, others permit or even require their usage, particularly for=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus" title=3D"Calculus">calc=
ulus</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trigonometry" title=
=3D"Trigonometry">trigonometry</a> classes. =20
</p><p>In 2022 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amplify_(company)" =
title=3D"Amplify (company)">Amplify</a> bought <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Desmos" title=3D"Desmos">Desmos</a> Education / Curriculum.<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:HP_Prime_Graphing_Calculator.jpg" class=3D"mw=
-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commo=
ns/thumb/4/46/HP_Prime_Graphing_Calculator.jpg/250px-HP_Prime_Graphing_Calc=
ulator.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"190" height=3D"380" class=3D"mw-fil=
e-element" data-file-width=3D"1900" data-file-height=3D"3803"></a><figcapti=
on><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HP_Prime" title=3D"HP Prime">HP=
 Prime</a>, a modern graphing calculator capable of doing Symbolic Manipula=
tion, Computer Algebra System (CAS)</figcaption></figure>
<ul><li><b>North America</b> =E2=80=93 high school mathematics teachers all=
ow and even encourage their students to use graphing calculators in class. =
In some cases (especially in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calcu=
lus" title=3D"Calculus">calculus</a> courses) they are <i>required</i>.<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calcu=
lator#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/College_Board" title=3D"Col=
lege Board">College Board</a> of the United States</b> =E2=80=93 permits th=
e use of most graphing calculators that do not have a <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/QWERTY" title=3D"QWERTY">QWERTY</a>-style keyboard for =
parts of its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Placement" t=
itle=3D"Advanced Placement">AP</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/SAT" title=3D"SAT">SAT</a> exams. CAS-equipped calculators are permitt=
ed on AP exams,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> howe=
ver they are not permitted on the SAT exams.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator=
#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ACT_=
(test)" title=3D"ACT (test)">ACT</a> exam and <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/International_Baccalaureate" title=3D"International Baccalaurea=
te">IB</a> schools do not permit the use of calculators with computer algeb=
ra systems.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Graphing_calculator#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphing_calculat=
or#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><b>United Kingdom</b> =E2=80=93 a graphing calculator is allowed for <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A-level" title=3D"A-level">A-level</=
a> maths courses, however they are not required and the exams are designed =
to be broadly 'calculator neutral'. Similarly, at <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/GCSE" title=3D"GCSE">GCSE</a>, all current courses include =
one paper where no calculator of any kind can be used, but students are per=
mitted to use graphical calculators for other papers. The use of graphical =
calculators at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GCSE" title=3D"GCSE=
">GCSE</a> is not widespread with cost being a likely factor. The use of <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_algebra_system" title=3D"Co=
mputer algebra system">CAS</a> is not allowed for either <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A-level" title=3D"A-level">A-level</a> or <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GCSE" title=3D"GCSE">GCSE</a>. Similarly, ca=
lculators with QWERTY keyboard layout are also not allowed as well.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
